ext\",\"text\":\"**Considering Exception Handling**\\n\\nI’m realizing that a custom nested exception may not be necessary after all. However, I need to think about reflection metadata on JDK class constructors; could the native implementation have built-in support? Dynamic metadata might require JDK reflection configuration, and an agent would need to collect that. There may be risks when reflecting on JDK class constructors if the metadata isn’t available. Using the standard wrapper with `UndeclaredThrowableException` aligns well with the documentation, even if it hasn't been filtered out properly.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering test engineer expectations**\\n\\nI’m thinking about what is typically expected from an expert JVM test engineer, particularly around high coverage in integration testing. It seems like having an active class in its own dedicated file might be necessary for proper organization and clarity. I want to make sure I’m aligning my approach with best practices in testing to ensure everything works correctly while meeting those high expectations.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_Ln8ps1d67xE9QDs50NxNNZhv|fc_09f2f27b208e51fd0169ef6495d01481a28f9b58ecbd6c0130", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/UndeclaredThrowableTransformerTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage cglib.cglib_nodep;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.UndeclaredThrowableException;\n\nimport net.sf.cglib.transform.impl.UndeclaredThrowableTransformer;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThatIllegalArgumentException;\n\npublic class UndeclaredThrowableTransformerTest {\n    @Test\n    void acceptsWrapperWithThrowableConstructor() {\n        UndeclaredThrowableTransformer transformer = new UndeclaredThrowableTransformer(\n                UndeclaredThrowableException.class);\n\n        assertThat(transformer).isNotNull();\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void rejectsWrapperWithoutThrowableConstructor() {\n        assertThatIllegalArgumentException()\n                .isThrownBy(() -> new UndeclaredThrowableTransformer(String.class))\n                .withMessageContaining(\"does not have a single-arg constructor that takes a Throwable\");\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 6980, "output": 1861, "cacheRead": 5632, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 14473, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777296511206, "responseId": "resp_09f2f27b208e51fd0169ef647f95e881a2a22e12803350fef0"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_Ln8ps1d67xE9QDs50NxNNZhv|fc_09f2f27b208e51fd0169ef6495d01481a28f9b58ecbd6c0130", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 1145 bytes to tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/UndeclaredThrowableTransformerTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777296535456}]}
